9:
Keep your guard up. There's no telling 
what lurks here.
12:
Can't believe we're in an actual 
haunted house.
15: ...You're not scared of ghosts, are you?
19:
No!
But I can feel a dark presence, large 
and growing larger...
26:
This is no time for jests. Danger is all 
around—
35:
The legs are uneven, and we've been 
stomping around on the floorboards, 
so...
44:
You truly do not find this place 
unnatural?
49: Th-the latch was broken, that's all.
53:
Ever since the Guild appointed us this 
task, my mind has been uneasy.
61:
I'm sure everything that just happened 
can be explained by the good old laws 
of phys—
92:
Maybe we should not have brought 
him here...
116:
I'm really sorry you got hurt protecting 
me.
120:
Oh, you're that kid.
Heh. Don't worry about it. 
I've had a lot worse.
127:
I can't believe a chandelier knocked 
me out. My powers must've weakened.
129:
*sigh* Explains how those poltergeists 
managed to start levitating things on 
my watch...
140:
Wait right here! I'll whip you up a bowl 
of nutrition!
145:
...Well, can't say I don't miss people 
food.
147: But... I really shouldn't be here. Right?
156: Hey, what's your name? I'm Alk!
158:
And, uh... Can you eat salt and garlic 
and stuff? It's not gonna exorcise you, 
is it?
163: I'm Andy. Thanks for taking care of me.
165:
...And go easy on the salt and garlic 
please.
